---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Wallet Automation · Actuali"
  description="Log tap-to-pay purchases from Apple Wallet into Actuali automatically with a Shortcuts automation."
>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-6">
    <header class="space-y-2">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">Log Wallet payments automatically</h1>
      <p class="text-neutral-500">
        Every time you tap to pay with Apple Wallet, a Shortcuts automation can log the purchase into Actuali in the
        background — no need to open the app.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="space-y-3">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">How it works</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-700">
        Actuali ships a <strong>Log Transaction</strong> action that any shortcut or automation can run — there is nothing
        to install. iOS lets you trigger an automation whenever a specific Wallet card is charged, so you connect the two:
        one automation per card, each passing the transaction's amount and merchant straight into your budget.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-3">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Before you start</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 text-neutral-700">
        <li>Install Actuali and connect it to your Actual Budget server.</li>
        <li>
          Set a <strong>Default Account</strong> in the app's Settings, or plan to pick an account in each automation (step
          6 below).
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-3">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Set it up</h2>
      <ol class="list-decimal space-y-2 pl-6 text-neutral-700">
        <li>Open the <strong>Shortcuts</strong> app and go to the <strong>Automation</strong> tab.</li>
        <img
          src="/wallet-automation/step-1.png"
          alt="iOS Wallet Automation - Step 1"
          class="my-2 w-full max-w-sm"
          loading="lazy"
        />
        <li>Create <strong>New Automation</strong>, then search and choose <strong>Wallet</strong>.</li>
        <img
          src="/wallet-automation/step-2.png"
          alt="iOS Wallet Automation - Step 2"
          class="my-2 w-full max-w-sm"
          loading="lazy"
        />
        <li>
          Select the Wallet card you want to track, keep <strong>Run Immediately</strong>, and tap <strong>Next</strong
          >.
        </li>
        <img
          src="/wallet-automation/step-3.png"
          alt="iOS Wallet Automation - Step 3"
          class="my-2 w-full max-w-sm"
          loading="lazy"
        />
        <li>Choose <strong>Create New Shortcut</strong></li>
        <img
          src="/wallet-automation/step-4.png"
          alt="iOS Wallet Automation - Step 4"
          class="my-2 w-full max-w-sm"
          loading="lazy"
        />
        <li>Tap <strong>Add Action</strong>, and search for <strong>Log Transaction</strong> from Actuali.</li>
        <img
          src="/wallet-automation/step-5.png"
          alt="iOS Wallet Automation - Step 5"
          class="my-2 w-full max-w-sm"
          loading="lazy"
        />
        <img
          src="/wallet-automation/step-6.png"
          alt="iOS Wallet Automation - Step 6"
          class="my-2 w-full max-w-sm rounded-xl"
          loading="lazy"
        />
        <li>
          Tap the action's <strong>Amount</strong> field, Tap <strong>Select Variable</strong>, Tap <strong
            >Shortcut Input</strong
          >. Then tap the <strong>Shortcut Input</strong> variable and change it to <strong>Amount</strong>.
        </li>
        <img
          src="/wallet-automation/step-7.png"
          alt="iOS Wallet Automation - Step 7"
          class="my-2 w-full max-w-sm"
          loading="lazy"
        />
        <img
          src="/wallet-automation/step-8.png"
          alt="iOS Wallet Automation - Step 8"
          class="my-2 w-full max-w-sm"
          loading="lazy"
        />
        <li>
          Repeat for <strong>Payee</strong>, tap on the <strong>Shortcut Input</strong> and change the variable to <strong
            >Merchant</strong
          >
          <i> (or Name)</i>.
        </li>

        <li>Tap <strong>Account</strong> and select the relevant Account from Actuali.</li>
      </ol>
      <p class="text-neutral-700 underline">Repeat for each card you want to track.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-700">
        From then on, tapping to pay logs the purchase automatically and Actuali confirms it with a notification.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-3">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Troubleshooting</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 text-neutral-700">
        <li>
          <strong>Nothing gets logged?</strong> Check that the automation is set to Run Immediately and that the Log Transaction
          action's Amount and Payee fields use the transaction's variables, not blank values.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>"No amount was received" notification?</strong> iOS occasionally runs the automation before Wallet has
          the transaction details. This depends on the card, bank, and terminal and is outside the app's control — add
          the transaction manually and it usually works again on the next tap.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>"No account" error notification?</strong> Set a Default Account in Actuali's Settings, or choose an Account
          inside the automation's action.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Wrong account?</strong> Each automation can target its own account — edit the automation and set the Account
          field to match the card.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-3">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Questions?</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-700">
        See the <a href="/support" class="underline hover:text-neutral-900">support page</a> or email
        <a href="mailto:actuali@mfazz.com" class="underline hover:text-neutral-900">actuali@mfazz.com</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>
